3ï¸âƒ£ Configuration & Settings

Where Git Integration Is Configured

Scope: Workspace level âœ…

Steps:

1. Workspace â†’ Settings
2. Enable Git integration
3. Connect to:
   - Azure DevOps OR
   - GitHub
4. Select:
   - Repository
   - Branch
   - Folder

Not configurable at:

- Domain level âŒ
- Notebook level âŒ

---

4ï¸âƒ£ How Git Integration Works

Sync Model (Important)

- Git is the source of truth
- Two main actions:
  - Commit â†’ Workspace âœ Git
  - Update / Sync â†’ Git âœ Workspace

Danger (exam favorite):

Pulling from Git can overwrite workspace artifacts

---

5ï¸âƒ£ What Fabric CAN and CANNOT Do

Fabric CAN:

- Commit workspace changes
- Pull latest changes from Git
- Track artifact metadata

Fabric CANNOT:

- Create or switch Git branches
- Resolve merge conflicts
- Auto-merge changes
- Enforce PR policies

All of the above must be done in GitHub / Azure DevOps

---

